cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.GT, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the development of computational intelligence (CI) and its relative strength in comparison with human intelligence for the game of Go. It also introduces the methods and techniques used in AlphaGo, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), game theory (cs.GT), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper's focus on AI and its application in Go suggests that cs.AI is the most likely sub-category.
